Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.62,0:01:46.37,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.75,0:01:49.00,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.01,0:02:06.98,ep-title-bg,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2000,0)\p1\blur1}m 0 0 l 950 0 950 100 0 100
Dialogue: 1,0:02:01.01,0:02:06.98,ep-title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1100,0)\be1}One-Eyed Fish
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.78,0:02:25.62,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see the Mushi, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.87,0:02:31.42,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.83,0:02:37.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ones that are still exposed\Nto light aren't very dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.34,0:02:41.39,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or is it me that you're afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.97,0:02:46.14,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Drink this. It'll be good for your wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.69,0:02:55.52,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get well and leave quickly. I'm\Nnot letting you stay for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.35,0:03:32.19,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.15,0:03:34.36,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.65,0:03:35.52,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.82,0:03:40.57,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strange, we must have come the wrong way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:42.24,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.70,0:03:47.24,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Yoki?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.24,0:03:49.58,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you seeing strange things again?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.08,0:03:55.88,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. Those are illusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.71,0:04:00.71,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.46,0:05:20.42,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.35,0:05:41.27,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can move a lot better now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.62,0:05:53.20,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what type of fish that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.20,0:05:57.33,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pale white with green eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.50,0:06:03.30,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each one of them has only one eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.30,0:06:05.30,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because of the Mushi in the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.59,0:06:09.64,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't go near the pond at night or in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.68,0:06:16.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those things aren't illusions, are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.23,0:06:22.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You couldn't say that they exist like we\Ndo nor that they're only illusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.15,0:06:25.19,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they do affect us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.03,0:06:28.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are they completely different from us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.49,0:06:33.33,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They exist in a different form, but\Nthey're completely unrelated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.12,0:06:37.08,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are a different manifestation of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.79,0:06:40.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.83,0:06:43.42,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.84,0:06:54.39,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can walk without a cane now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.81,0:07:04.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoki,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.44,0:07:09.45,dialogue,,0,0,0,,your foot is better now, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.45,0:07:12.32,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have a place to return to, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.20,0:07:17.70,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't have a place to go back to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.20,0:07:22.17,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I traveled with my mom, selling things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.13,0:07:27.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, my foot still hurts when I walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.09,0:07:32.13,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.34,0:07:38.64,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, the Mushi in the pond, what's it like? Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.02,0:07:42.94,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.48,0:07:48.53,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Its appearance can only be described as "darkness".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.24,0:07:51.20,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Darkness?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.32,0:07:53.91,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there are two types of darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.16,0:07:58.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,One is inside a shed; a moonless night;\Nor when you close your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.91,0:08:01.91,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the darkness that is made when you obstruct light.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.67,0:08:05.96,notes,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,0)}Toko no Yami: eternal darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.67,0:08:05.96,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other is the "Toko no Yami".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.34,0:08:12.97,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It stays in the shade during the day, but at night\Nit leaves the pond to eat small Mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.18,0:08:17.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did your hair, your eyes and\Nthe fish all become like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.56,0:08:23.06,dialogue,,0,0,0,,At dawn, the pond often shines silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:27.69,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must be reducing consumed Mushi to light.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.94,0:08:32.24,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This seems to be the result of being\Nexposed to it too many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.74,0:08:37.03,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't you lose your other eye then, if you stay here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.45,0:08:39.28,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've seen the fish in the pond, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.87,0:08:42.08,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strangely, there are no fish missing both eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.45,0:08:44.58,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That must be the way it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.12,0:08:48.09,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, it's getting dark. Let's go inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.29,0:08:50.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is the Mushi called?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.09,0:08:57.01,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dark ones are called "Tokoyami".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.59,0:09:01.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ones that give off light seem to be a different\Ntype of Mushi living on the Tokoyami.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.68,0:09:03.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know if they have a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.35,0:09:07.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Personally, I call them "Ginko".
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.36,0:09:14.36,dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.53,0:09:16.74,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:17.57,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This one then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.16,0:09:19.58,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try taking a bite.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.58,0:09:21.95,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't swallow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.87,0:09:23.66,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.79,0:09:27.29,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.79,0:09:31.38,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It won't kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.38,0:09:33.76,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep it up and you'll have a strong stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.76,0:09:35.22,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.47,0:09:38.97,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're all lumped together.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.15,0:09:51.69,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you scatter them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.69,0:09:53.40,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'll bunch up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.40,0:09:56.49,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's always like this where I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.49,0:09:58.36,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, can I do it too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.36,0:10:00.53,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not doing it for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.87,0:10:01.74,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.20,0:10:04.54,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a bit bitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.18,0:10:20.97,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nui.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.26,0:10:23.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's light the lamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.06,0:10:25.52,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:32.36,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I forgot, I can see well in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.73,0:10:34.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of the Ginko?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.48,0:10:37.70,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably. Well, it's useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.45,0:10:42.66,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Yoki.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.49,0:10:46.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you walk the paths alone at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.16,0:10:51.58,dialogue,,0,0,0,,sometimes the stars and the moon\Nlighting your way disappear,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.92,0:10:56.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and you become disoriented.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.01,0:11:00.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.22,0:11:06.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if when that happens you can't remember\Nyour name or your own past,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.64,0:11:09.64,dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's because a Tokoyami is close by.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.48,0:11:13.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's said that you can escape if\Nyou can somehow remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.69,0:11:16.90,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if you can't remember at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.19,0:11:20.95,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give yourself a name – any name\Nthat comes to mind, they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.20,0:11:22.45,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sure that works?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.82,0:11:29.04,dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, they say you won't remember anything\Nfrom when you had your past name.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.29,0:11:34.00,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.09,0:11:39.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you why you're here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.47,0:11:43.64,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.39,0:11:49.06,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beyond this mountain is my home village.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.23,0:11:53.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's isolated, but it's a beautiful village.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.86,0:11:58.40,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was born with a tendency to attract Mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.78,0:12:05.62,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't stay in one place, so I traveled\Nthrough villages as a "Mushi-shi".
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.12,0:12:10.04,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet, I made frequent trips home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.91,0:12:16.38,dialogue,,0,0,0,,To meet my parents, my friends... and\Nmost of all, my husband and my child.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.42,0:12:18.21,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.09,0:12:24.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband and child were missing in the mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.68,0:12:28.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,along with my father, my friends and other\Nvillagers that went looking for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.97,0:12:34.85,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I ran through the mountains to find them and\Neventually learned that living in this pond...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.10,0:12:36.98,dialogue,,0,0,0,,is a Tokoyami.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.36,0:12:43.07,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've learned from other Mushi-shi what happens\Nwhen you're taken by a Tokoyami,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.07,0:12:45.49,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and what you should do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.49,0:12:56.00,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I stay here, in hopes that they're\Nstill wandering somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.38,0:13:01.09,dialogue,,0,0,0,,How long have you been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.09,0:13:03.92,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Six years, more or less.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.68,0:13:06.39,dialogue,,0,0,0,,All alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.14,0:13:12.89,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those people... I wonder if they all look like you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.89,0:13:15.14,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.52,0:13:18.19,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll help you look for them. Can't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.52,0:13:19.57,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So let me stay...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.57,0:13:20.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:24.45,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not? Why can't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.95,0:13:30.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to do this alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.37,0:13:33.00,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.20,0:13:35.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't make it an excuse to stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.42,0:13:38.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speak of it again...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.50,0:13:41.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and I'll throw you out immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.36,0:14:09.20,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nui's hiding something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.45,0:14:12.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There must be a reason I can't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.91,0:14:15.20,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come out, Tokoyami, Ginko.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.40,0:14:40.94,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that fish?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.56,0:14:43.90,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's losing its eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.33,0:14:56.29,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.83,0:14:57.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.71,0:15:02.17,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing? I told you not to go near the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.17,0:15:02.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nui.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.13,0:15:07.80,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason the fish only have one eye... is because\Nthey vanish once both of their eyes are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.55,0:15:10.43,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.39,0:15:13.89,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They aren't vanishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.26,0:15:18.56,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The light that the Ginko give off\Nturns them into Tokoyami.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.56,0:15:20.23,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.23,0:15:22.94,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why'd you just leave it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.11,0:15:27.40,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're a Mushi-shi, aren't you? Why are\Nyou letting such a horrible Mushi live?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.94,0:15:32.45,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't let yourself be blinded by fear or anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.20,0:15:37.70,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything is only as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.79,0:15:43.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should just use our conscience\Nto escape from what we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.88,0:15:51.26,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is what we Mushi-shi have been\Nstudying to do since long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.43,0:15:55.39,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I kept many records of the Ginko.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.97,0:15:59.06,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And by the time I discovered the fate of the fish...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.64,0:16:02.94,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd already been exposed to the light too many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.02,0:16:10.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've tried moving the one-eyed fish from the\Npond to keep them away from the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.28,0:16:21.12,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once it started, they eventually lost both eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.58,0:16:23.37,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and became the Tokoyami.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.79,0:16:24.88,dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.33,0:16:26.71,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.96,0:16:32.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet I still couldn't accept the fact that my husband\Nand child had become the Tokoyami.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.72,0:16:37.22,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I roamed in search, always avoiding the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.14,0:16:46.73,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But... some time ago, I came to\Nrealize that everything is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.19,0:16:50.28,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.69,0:16:54.20,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoki, leave now, if you understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.20,0:16:56.20,dialogue,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.20,0:16:58.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's got to be something we can do. Let's leave here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.78,0:17:00.41,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be a fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.33,0:17:07.92,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing that can be done, and\NI was always content with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.46,0:17:11.42,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But with you here, it's been nothing but painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.64,0:17:18.93,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.10,0:17:22.18,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll be able to live your life traveling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.64,0:17:26.52,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're fortunate not to have a place to call home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.81,0:17:27.69,dialogue,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.86,0:17:29.77,dialogue,,0,0,0,,My home is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.77,0:17:31.69,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been here the longest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.69,0:17:35.74,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not. This is the place for the Tokoyami and I.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.49,0:17:38.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not your place to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.94,0:18:12.32,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is how it should be, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.62,0:18:25.62,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The pond...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.37,0:18:27.08,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nui!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.58,0:18:30.79,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't go! Don't go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.42,0:18:37.55,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nui?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.01,0:18:39.22,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.30,0:18:41.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.72,0:18:42.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nui!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.69,0:18:50.85,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What have you done?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.24,0:18:59.24,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nui? It's you, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.82,0:19:01.07,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.24,0:19:02.37,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.53,0:19:04.70,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I... will soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.33,0:19:11.08,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Ginko are going to awaken soon.\NGo as far away as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.75,0:19:13.29,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.34,0:19:17.46,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your hand has no heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.67,0:19:21.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's neither cold nor warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.59,0:19:24.26,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your hand is still warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.01,0:19:26.27,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not just your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.56,0:19:34.27,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I no longer have eyes but when your eyes look\Nthis way they are as warm as the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.02,0:19:40.20,dialogue,,0,0,0,,How nostalgic that was, in the darkness by the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.53,0:19:44.28,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, Yoki, close one eye for the rest of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.08,0:19:49.71,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give the other one to the Ginko so that\Nyou can escape from the Tokoyami.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.33,0:19:56.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But shut the other one tightly so that\Nyou may see the light of day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.71,0:20:00.30,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.42,0:20:02.30,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Ginko are going to awaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.65,0:20:20.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's the Ginko.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.65,0:20:25.91,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The eyeless fish in the pits of the Tokoyami.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.04,0:20:31.54,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't let yourself be blinded by fear or anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.29,0:20:36.67,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Everything is only as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.72,0:20:49.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can smell the dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.98,0:21:00.36,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The moon again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.78,0:21:05.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,How many times has it been now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.12,0:21:08.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.79,0:21:13.04,dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.12,0:21:17.92,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was I supposed to do when this happens again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.30,0:21:25.55,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The next morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.27,0:21:34.56,dialogue,,0,0,0,,my right eye saw the light of day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.57,0:21:41.98,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's up with you? I haven't seen you around.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.65,0:21:44.07,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.37,0:21:50.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Yo, I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.16,0:21:53.54,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}You sure you should be up? Don't strain yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.54,0:21:54.25,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.25,0:21:55.21,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}How're you doing now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.21,0:21:58.08,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Have you remembered anything other than your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.63,0:22:00.59,dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.71,0:22:04.01,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well that's fine. You can live here if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.01,0:22:07.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go see the village chief tomorrow, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.18,0:22:09.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.81,0:22:18.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,My left eye was dark even under sunlight, as\Nif it was replaced with a scoop of darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.19,0:22:22.61,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It attracted strange things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.36,0:22:31.41,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had the feeling that they'd bring disaster\Nif I continued to draw them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.29,0:22:35.54,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ginko, time for breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.33,0:22:41.29,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ginko, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.46,0:22:44.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where'd he go off to?
